# MediaPipe Installation and Model Download Plan

## Goal Description
The user wants to install the MediaPipe library and the specific Hand Landmarker model file ("handliandmaerker") referenced in their notebook. This will enable them to run the Jupyter notebook [hand_landmarker.ipynb](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/hand_landmarker.ipynb) or use the model in their python scripts.

## User Review Required
None.

## Proposed Changes
### Dependencies
- Install `mediapipe` via pip.

### Files
#### [NEW] [hand_landmarker.task](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/hand_landmarker.task)
- Download from `https://storage.googleapis.com/mediapipe-models/hand_landmarker/hand_landmarker/float16/1/hand_landmarker.task`

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Run `python -c "import mediapipe; print(mediapipe.__version__)"` to verify installation.
- Check file size/presence of `hand_landmarker.task`.
